Widget-level notes:
- **Control Buttons** are disabled/greyed appropriately: only one of {Manual, Autonomous, Hybrid Auto} can be enabled-and-clickable at a time; ArUco Debug and Git Update are independent of the driving-mode exclusivity group but ArUco Debug should still be blocked while a driving mode is running **if** it needs the camera (it does), so it belongs in the same mutual-exclusion group for camera ownership even though it's not a "driving" mode per se — call this out to the reviewer as a design decision, see Section 6.
- **Camera Preview** is always visible; when idle, it shows the live feed from the launcher's own lightweight camera open; when a camera-owning mode is running, it shows a static placeholder frame plus a caption ("Camera in use by Autonomous Driving") rather than fighting for the device — this directly implements the Section 7 arbitration rule.
- **Terminal Output** never blocks the UI thread — all appends happen via Qt signals emitted from a background reader, not by polling in the UI thread.
- **Error Notifications** are non-modal (no blocking dialog boxes) so a crash in one mode never freezes control over the rest of the app.

