## 8. Logging Strategy

- **Capture**: `QProcess.readyReadStandardOutput` / `readyReadStandardError` signals, read via `readAllStandardOutput()`/`readAllStandardError()`, decoded UTF-8 with `errors="replace"` (child scripts may emit non-ASCII, e.g. the "—" em-dash seen in `drive_auto.py`/`main_auto.py` log format strings).
- **Tagging**: every line is wrapped with `(mode_name, stream, timestamp, text)` before entering `log_manager`, so the Terminal Output widget's per-mode tabs and the "All" combined view can both be fed from one buffer.
- **Timestamps**: launcher adds its own wall-clock timestamp at receipt time (children already timestamp their own `logging.basicConfig` output internally, e.g. `[%(asctime)s]`, but the launcher should not rely on parsing that — treat child output as opaque text and prefix its own timestamp for consistent sorting across concurrently running modes).
- **Colored logs**: simple substring/regex severity detection (`ERROR`, `WARN`, `Traceback`) mapped to text color in the `TerminalOutputWidget` (Qt `QTextEdit` with `QTextCharFormat` per line) — cosmetic only, does not require parsing children's log format precisely.
- **Filtering**: a per-tab search/filter `QLineEdit` above each terminal view, filtering the ring buffer client-side (no need to re-run processes).
- **File persistence**: `log_manager` mirrors every received line to `logs/<mode>_<YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS>.log` (new file per process **start**, not per launcher session, so restarts get fresh files and old runs are never overwritten) — `logs/` added to `.gitignore` (existing `.gitignore` file would need exactly one line added here; only trivial exception to "no existing file changes").
- **Retention**: simple size/count cap (e.g., keep last 20 log files per mode) cleaned up on launcher startup — avoids unbounded disk growth on a Pi's typically small SD card/eMMC.

---

## 9. Error Handling Strategy

- **Camera conflicts**: `camera_bridge` centralizes all camera open attempts; any `RuntimeError` from `Camera.start()` (it already raises `"[Camera] No frame received within timeout."` per the inspected source) is caught and surfaced as a non-blocking Error Notification, not a crash of the launcher.
- **Process launch failures** (`QProcess.errorOccurred`, e.g. `FailedToStart` if a script path is wrong or Python env is missing a dependency): shown in the Error Notification bar with the raw error text and a "View Log" link.
- **Crash vs. clean exit**: distinguished via `QProcess.ExitStatus` plus exit code; only non-zero/crash exits produce a notification — a clean `Q`/`ESC` quit from inside `drive_auto.py`'s own loop should be a quiet "Stopped" state change, not an alarming error banner.
- **GPIO/hardware unavailable**: `motor_controller.py` already logs `"[Motor] gpiozero import failed"` / `"[Motor] GPIO stack unavailable. Motors disabled."` to its own stdout/stderr when hardware is missing (e.g., developing on a non-Pi machine) — the launcher does not need new detection logic, it just needs to make sure this line isn't lost: `log_manager`'s Hardware Status panel can do a simple substring watch (`"GPIO stack unavailable"`, `"gpiozero import failed"`) on incoming log lines to flip a status badge, as a nice-to-have (Phase 3), without needing to parse or import `motor_controller.py` itself.
- **Never let a child-process problem block the UI thread**: all reads happen via signals (Section 6); any exception inside a Qt slot handling those signals must be caught locally and logged rather than propagating and freezing the event loop.
- **Shutdown of the launcher itself**: on window close, `process_manager` must attempt graceful stop (Section 6) of any still-running mode before the launcher process exits, with a short timeout, to avoid orphaning a driving process with motors still engaged.

