## 10. Implementation Phases

Each phase should be independently reviewable and shippable; later phases depend only on earlier ones.

**Phase 0 — Scaffolding**
- Create `launcher/` package skeleton, `mode_registry.py` with the 4–5 mode table (data only, no logic), `settings.py`, empty `ui_main_window.py` that just shows the mode table read-only. No process launching yet.

**Phase 1 — Process lifecycle (no camera, no fancy UI)**
- Implement `process_manager.py` with `QProcess`-based start/stop/restart/crash-detection.
- Wire Control Buttons + Process Status Table only (Section 5, minus camera preview).
- Enforce mutual exclusion for the driving-mode group.

**Phase 2 — Logging**
- Implement `log_manager.py`, Terminal Output widget (tabs, filter, color), file persistence.
- Wire Error Notification bar for crash/launch-failure cases (Section 9).

**Phase 3 — Git Update panel**
- Implement `git_updater.py` (`git pull`, streamed through the same log channel tagged `"git"`), Git Update Panel UI, success/failure banner.

**Phase 4 — Camera preview (Option A)**
- Implement `camera_bridge.py` idle-only preview per Section 7 Option A.
- Extend mutual exclusion to the camera-owning group (adds `aruco_debug` + `launcher_preview` itself into that group).

**Phase 5 — Hardware Status polish (optional, nice-to-have)**
- Lightweight log-substring watchers for GPIO/IMU/PS4 status badges (Section 9).
- `psutil`-based CPU/RAM display if desired.

**Phase 6 — (Separately scoped, requires explicit approval) Camera-during-driving preview (Option B)** and/or **eliminating `cv2.imshow` in `drive_auto.py`/`main_auto.py` (Option C)** — both involve real modifications to existing hardware-facing files and must not be bundled into the initial launcher delivery.

