## 12. Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| **`aruco_knowledge.py` does not exist in the repo** (confirmed by full-text search of the provided source). | **Open question — do not implement until resolved.** Either the user provides the real path/name, or an implementation agent authors a new thin wrapper around `ArUco/aruco_detector.py` with explicit sign-off, since it would be new car-facing code, not pure orchestration. |
| Camera device contention (two processes opening the same USB/Picamera2 device). | `camera_bridge` is the single arbiter; launcher never opens its own camera while any camera-owning mode is active (Section 7, Option A). |
| GPIO pin contention across concurrently running driving modes. | Mutual exclusion group enforced by `process_manager` before `start()` is ever called (Section 6). |
| Child process ignoring `SIGTERM`/hanging on shutdown (e.g., blocked on a `cv2.waitKey`/hardware read). | Escalation ladder: `SIGINT` → wait → `SIGTERM` → wait → `SIGKILL`, each with a bounded timeout, so the launcher never hangs indefinitely on `process.stop()`. |
| Race condition: user rapid-clicks Start/Stop/Restart. | All state transitions gated through `process_manager`'s single state dict guarded by checks on current `ProcessState` (not just UI button `enabled` flags, which can lag actual process state). |
| Blocking UI thread from slow file I/O (writing every log line to disk synchronously). | Buffer log lines and flush to disk on a `QTimer` (e.g., every 250ms) or from a dedicated writer thread, never inline in the Qt slot handling `readyRead*`. |
| `drive_auto.py`/`main_auto.py` requiring a display (`cv2.imshow`) when launched headlessly via `QProcess` (e.g., over SSH without X forwarding). | Pre-existing constraint, not introduced by the launcher; surfaced via stderr capture into an Error Notification rather than a silent hang. Long-term fix is the separately-scoped Option C in Section 7/Phase 6. |
| Thread safety of `Camera._frame` access from the launcher's preview timer vs. its own internal capture thread. | Already handled inside `Camera` itself via `threading.Lock()` around `_frame` (confirmed in inspected source) — the launcher just calls the existing thread-safe `.frame` property, no new locking needed. |
| Disk space exhaustion from log files on a small SD card. | Retention cap + rotation policy (Section 8). |
| Adding a heavy GUI dependency (PySide6, ~150MB+) to a resource-constrained Pi. | Document as a deliberate tradeoff in Section 6/13; if this proves too heavy in practice on the target Pi model, CustomTkinter is the documented fallback (Section 6), at the cost of losing native `QProcess` async I/O and needing manual reader threads instead. |

