# 🏗️ Project Organization & Improvements

This document outlines suggestions for improving the clarity, maintainability, and structure of the Smart Car project.

## 📂 Suggested Folder Structure
To improve clarity, consider organizing the root directory as follows:

```text
smart-car/
├── core/                # Hardware abstraction layers
│   ├── camera.py
│   ├── motor_controller.py
│   ├── imu_reader.py
│   └── ps4_controller.py
├── data_utils/          # Replaced 'validationData'
│   ├── merge_datasets.py
│   ├── clean_missing_images.py
│   └── optimize_dataset.py
├── scripts/             # Utility scripts and diagnostics
│   ├── motor_calibration.py
│   └── synchronized_sampler.py
├── training/            # AI Training pipeline (Keep as is)
├── analyze/             # Data analysis tools (Keep as is)
├── models/              # Saved models (Keep as is)
├── config.py            # Global configuration
├── collect_data.py      # Entry point: Manual
└── drive_auto.py        # Entry point: Autonomous
```

## 🛠️ Recommended Code Improvements

### 1. Standardize Path Handling
Many scripts currently have hardcoded paths (e.g., `D:\coding\...`). These should be replaced with relative paths or command-line arguments using `argparse`.
- **Affected Files:** `analyze/analyze_dataset.py`, `validationData/merge_datasets.py`.

### 2. Environment Configuration
